    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors at Model Risk Level 5 for the Class III VAD hemolysis prediction. Seven factors were formally assessed; all seven achieved levels below required levels. Six factors were flagged as not-assessed epistemic gaps. The cumulative credibility shortfall is substantial and the model does not meet the evidentiary threshold for regulatory submission in the VAD indication. The package is filed under the Minimal conformance profile with hash integrity protection; digital signature application is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow.",
